Diagnosis . Adults of
Neothalassius
are easily distinguished from other parathalassiine genera by the head with well-developed parafacial plate; gena distinctly projected below eye (
Figs 9–12
); mouthparts directed posteriorly with narrow labellum and broad flat palpus (
Figs 3
, 5 ,
9–12
); wing veins M 2 , dm-m and cell dm absent (Fig. 13 ); fore coxa spinose (
Fig. 5
); tarsomere 5 of all legs with dorso-medial projection (
Fig. 4
); and abdominal sternite 1 with medial projection on the anterior margin (
Fig. 7
).
